cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with tracking and discovering exceptions in aggregate queries over dynamic hidden web databases, which involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the challenges of adhering to query-count limitations enforced by hidden web databases providers, which relates to security and cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in terms of developing efficient algorithms.
